Description: Up for auction here is an official Fender Stratocaster neck dated by serial number range S880000-S989999 to year 1980, which is bolted onto an aftermarket Stratocaster shaped body, guessing from the same year. It was an original 3 bolt tilt-neck modified/drilled with 4 holes to mate with the guitar body. That work was done well before I purchased the guitar. I purchased the guitar in 1989.Features:Original Fender machine head/tuners. 5-way pick-up selector switch. Master Volume control. Tone control as middle knob and official Fender TBX Tone control as the last knob. Official Fender Vintage Tremelo system purchased/installed new in 1990, E to E string measures 2 & 7/32nd inches wide. Contains three (3) single coil Fender Lace Sensor pickups purchased/installed new in 1990. Bridge Pickup: Lace Sensor-Red Guitar Pickup: The hottest output of the Sensor Series. Perfect for the bridge position when fat, punchy humbucking output. Middle Pickup: Lace Sensor-Silver Guitar Pickup: A fat 70's single-coil sound with increased output and more midrange. Neck Pickup: Lace Sensor-Blue Guitar Pickup: Slightly increased output with the warmer 50's humbucking sound in a single-coil configuration. Includes black Fender Logo molded plastic hard shell case.The guitar is in very good clean condition. Super shiny red finish. See all pictures of the guitar. Plays and sounds great.* Small nick in bottom edge of headstock below the 'S' of serial number and a small ding on the body where the forearm would rest while playing. Shipping is $50. (Lower 48 United States only) Pay Pal accepted only. Thanks for looking.
Title: Fender Stratocaster neck dated 1980 on a Strat body, Lace Sensor pickups w/ HSC
